<subSubSection pageId="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,639,1362,1729]" pageId="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,280,1655,1676]" pageId="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguishable from superficially similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[350,451,1681,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orellana">
<emphasis box="[350,451,1681,1702]" italics="true" pageId="12">P. orellana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dark brown coloration of the elytral apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[685,1172,194,879]" pageId="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,898,194,215]" pageId="12">Description. Size</emphasis>
: Length 
<quantity box="[1006,1095,194,215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="12" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; width 2.0 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[786,844,221,242]" pageId="12">Form</emphasis>
: As in 
<figureCitation box="[935,1027,221,242]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="22.[175,215,1444,1463]" captionTargetBox="[167,1157,203,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-120@22.[167,1157,192,1421]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs. 98–103. Pujoliclerus species, habitus. 98) P. ovatus; 99) P. wappesi; 100) P. amplus; 101) P. flavoapicalus;" pageId="12">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1043,1165,221,242]" pageId="12">Integument</emphasis>
: Head mostly yellow, epicranium with rectangular black marking, lower frons yellow; antenna black; pronotum bicolorous, anterior angles yellow, remainder black; elytra light brown, epipleural and sutural margins and apex more yellow; legs mostly yellow, infuscated; pterothorax and abdomen brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[769,825,407,428]" pageId="12">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes slightly wider than frons (13:10); funicular antennomeres very expanded, 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[698,712,454,468]" fontSize="6" pageId="12">th</superScript>
antennomere very large (
<figureCitation box="[985,1065,460,481]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[175,216,1487,1506]" captionTargetBox="[167,1170,207,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[151,1172,183,1487]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 21–38. Pujoliclerus species, antennae. 21) P. helvinus; 22) P. maracayensis; 23) P. bilineatus; 24) P. calceatus; 25) P. corumba; 26) P. ovatus; 27) P. wappesi; 28) P. amplus; 29) P. flavoapicalus; 30) P. gilvus; 31) P. hermani; 32) P. alajuela; 33) P. orellana; 34) P. megacavus; 35) P. oxinus; 36) P. alboordinus; 37) P. apolegmus; 38) P. catarina." pageId="12">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1088,1165,460,481]" pageId="12">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum quadrate (37:37), lateral tubercle prominent (
<figureCitation box="[742,816,513,534]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[175,215,1395,1414]" captionTargetBox="[151,1155,183,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-114@18.[151,1172,183,1383]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs. 48–61. Pujoliclerus species, pronota. 48) P. helvinus; 49) P. maracayensis; 50) P. modestus; 51) P. bilineatus; 52) P. calceatus; 53) P. corumba; 54) P. flavolimbatus; 55) P. ovatus; 56) P. wappesi; 57) P. amplus; 58) P. flavoapicalus; 59) P. gilvus; 60) P. hermani; 61) P. orellana." pageId="12">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
); epipleural fold gradually narrowed to elytral apex, asetiferous punctures prominent to elytral half. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[807,906,566,587]" pageId="12">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Aedeagus not available.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[685,1172,194,879]" pageId="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,810,593,614]" pageId="12">Variation.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[876,966,593,614]" pageId="12">paratype</typeStatus>
collected in PNN Gorgona has the elytra more yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[685,1172,194,879]" pageId="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,877,646,667]" pageId="12">Natural History.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[936,1019,646,667]" pageId="12">holotype</typeStatus>
and a 
<typeStatus box="[1090,1171,646,667]" pageId="12">paratype</typeStatus>
were collected during a time span between 
<date box="[685,886,699,720]" pageId="12" value="2001-12-11">11 December 2001</date>
and 
<date box="[946,1125,699,720]" pageId="12" value="2002-01-18">18 January 2002</date>
; the second 
<typeStatus box="[764,847,725,746]" pageId="12">paratype</typeStatus>
was taken during July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
